Summary: Run java to test Android functions
Description:
Maybe a design bug, maybe a feature request:

I want to run a Java class to test pieces of an Android application's functionality: (read/write data to file). If I execute within the Android module, I get Stub! errors. If I install or emulate it is very slow (I'm testing a specific piece).

If I include the Android module as a Module Dependency, it builds the Android files and I get a Stub! error during execution. But if I only include the classes directory and set as Provided, I get errors when Log.<x> is called.

Is there a proper way to run simple Java tests on components of an Android application (not using Activity, etc)?

Summary: AppCode still handles edits to project files incorrectly
Description:
I've run into this issue both when editing the file manually (say, doing a diff and reverting certain changes) and when updating from VCS.  Example scenarios:

1) I have a locally modified project.pbxproj
2) I update from VCS.
3) I either do automatic or manual resolve
4) AppCode ignores the updated project file.


Other scenario:

1) I have a locally modified project.pbxproj
2) I diff against "have revision" and revert some changes.
3) I finish the diff, and AppCode throws away my changes.

Very serious since it can silently break builds and cause major merge / project file issues.

Summary: Build might have "... is not fully resolved, using as is." warning with values with percentage signs that are reported from previous builds (e.g. NLSPATH case)
Description:
If finish build parameters have percentage signs, they will be tried to be interpreted as references when used as dep.

Seems, the properties returned from a finish build should contain no references (all references should be escaped) and they should not be tried to be resolved anymore.

An example of default property with percentages on Linux: env.NLSPATH=    /usr/dt/lib/nls/msg/%L/%N.cat

Summary: Silverlight - Incorrectly suggesting to convert property to private when used in binding expression
RVM + Command line runner
Description:
I recently upgraded to 6.0 and I'm psyched to see all of the rvm support, specifically the rvm ruby and gemset support for the rake runner and the ruby environment build feature.  There's one missing piece though, supporting rvm for the command line runner.

I have build plans and steps that invoke executables that are installed along with gems.  Some examples include cap (capistrano), bundle (bundler), and rspec.  There are other executables that are installed when gems are installed and it's not that uncommon to invoke them as part of a build.  A common build chain for our projects looks like this:

1) bundle install [command line runner]
2) rake spec [rake runner]
3) selenium script [command line runner]
4) cap deploy [command line runner]

All of those steps depend on a specific rvm ruby and gemset.  There's currently no way to set the rvm ruby and gemset in one place for all of those steps.  The ruby environment build feature only applies to the rake runner.  In the above example, that's only one step.

There is an rvm command called "rvm-shell" that takes an argument for the ruby and gemset and executes a command given that env.  For example:

{code}
$ rvm-shell ruby-1.9.2@alder -c 'ruby -v; rvm gemset name'
ruby 1.9.2p0 (2010-08-18 revision 29036) [x86_64-darwin10.5.0]
alder
{code}

Using rvm-shell automatically for command line runners if the build plan includes the ruby environment build feature would solve the problem in an intuitive way without requiring additional options.  If that's too magic, then there could be an option on the command line runner screen, or a new runner called rvm-shell.

To be clear, my ultimate goal is to reduce the number of places where the rvm ruby and gemset are explicitly called out.  The ideal would be to set it once and have all aspects of the build use that setting, whether the step is using rake, a custom shell script, or one of the many executables installed by gems.  When that's possible in an easy and intuitive way, TeamCity's support for ruby projects will be officially kick ass.  That along with TW-14493 would be extra awesome.

Summary: Ability to Vote on own issue
Description:
Currently, the reporter of an issue is unable to vote for that issue. This hinders the use of votes as a prioritization mechanism. We would like to use votes like powerdots which means any one can vote for any issue (a la uservoice). [Did I just say UserVoice on YouTrack's website?]

Please enable the ability of the reporter of an issue to vote on their reported issues.

Summary: Scope not showing in Freemarker file
Description:
In a Freemarker template (containing html), I'm not getting the bracket showing the current scope when the cursor is on the opening '<'.  The "Highlight current scope" option is set.  I can see the bracket flashing very quickly before disappearing.

The highlight ''is'' working in css and html files, as you can see in the attached screenshot.

Summary: Goto Class dialog is dismissed when the list of matched classes reduces and causes loss of mouse focus
Description:
Seeing this on Linux (Debian x86_64, XFCE desktop).  Steps to repro:

1. position the mouse cursor near the centre of the screen so that it will appear on top of the class choice list
2. Ctrl+n
3. start typing a class name that will initially give lots of matches (enough that the list appears underneath the cursor
4. continue typing to reduce the number of matches
5. when the choice list reduces in size sufficiently that it's no longer under the cursor I see the whole dialog disappear immediately.

Summary: Support OpenJDK
Description:
Sun SDK is not more... now there is Oracle's ... so you are still asking to run with the old Sun or the new Oracle's version?

Still I think it would be great to support the use of the open alternative instead

BTW: neither Sun's nor Oracle's can be found on any Ubuntu or Debian official repository... so invest in oss

Summary: recogenise relative class names in PhpDoc
email integration should trim out email thread to make comments shorter
Description: Can you please look at adding an option for the incoming email processor to clip off the email thread of an incoming email.  This would make the comments much shorter and easier to read.  It is quite easy to implement if you adhere to the MIME headers, and just process the first segment of an email, skipping the other sections.

Summary: When generating comment from email reply, don't include quoted text
Description: Most ticket systems include a string or lines of "=" that separate the message you are sending from the previous quoted email. As it is now in 3.0 when I reply to a notification it includes all the junk in the email with my comment which is usually not useful to have attached to the bug. Thanks!

Summary: Adjust Namespaces adds x:class attributes to xaml files
Description:
I executed the "Adjust namespaces" refactoring on one of my projects. The project also contains several xaml files that contain resource dictionaries with graphics, styles and data templates.

Current Behavior:
After I executed "Adjust namespaces", ReSharper added x:Class attributes to the resource dictionaries:

<ResourceDictionary xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
                    xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
                    x:Class="NLocalize.UI.Icons.f__nlocalize_src_trunk_nlocalize_ui_icons_excel_export_xaml">


Expected Behavior:
ReSharper should not add the x:Class attributes to these xaml files. It should only change x:Class attributes for xaml elements that already have x:Class attributes; it should never add new x:Class attributes.

Summary: struts.xml: support params passed to results
Description:
You can pass param to result using action's getter. Example from guide:
{code:xml}
<action name="fragment" class="FragmentAction">
    <result name="next" type="redirectAction">${nextAction}</result>
</action>
{code}
When I do CTRL+SPACE right after "${" -- I want to see all action's getters.

Summary: Externalize all settings to a file so they can be shared
Description:
For team collaboration, it would be great if all the settings could be exported to a file and automatically imported when the file changes (or when Dev Studio restarts).  

Today, any changes to 'Inspection Severity' or other settings have to be done on every machine - this is unmanageable for a large group that wants consistent settings.

Also, only the code style settings can be externalized today.  My team has checked a file into source control but it is still a manual step that every engineer has to do to load that file whenever it changes (even though they already have the new file because they got it when they got the latest code)

It is desirable for all settings (code style, inspection serverity, etc) to be externalized to a file that is automatically loaded when it changes or when dev studio restarts.

I have a FlashBuilder Library project that I imported as an Astella module.  I configured my "test" directory as a "test sources" folder in the module settings.

It seems as though Astella is not correctly picking up tests that already exist.

Summary: Run Configurations: for non-executable targets (e.g. aggregative)
Description:
I can't figure out any way to build any target that's not an executable producing target.

In Xcode, I frequently have targets set up like this:

- Dependencies (aggregate target of targets in sub-projects)
- My App (just the application, with no target dependencies)
- My App Build All (aggregate target containing Dependencies and MyApp)

And I use the "My App Build All" target as my main working target.

In AppCode, the only targets presented in the Run/Debug config editor are executable-producing targets. Xcode allows you to pick your "Active Executable" (the menu for which appears to be gathered from targets that output executables.) You separately choose your "Active Target" which is the target that gets build when you issue a Build command. When you issue a Run command, what's run is the Active Executable. Naturally, if the executable doesn't exist in the build products, the Run commands are disabled.

Example project attached.

Summary: Allow executing any targets
Description: Right now AppCode limits valid build targets to libraries and executables. My project has other targets, either for running scripts or as meta-targets executing other targets via dependencies. There's no way to execute these from AppCode except making a custom xcodebuild command and run it from the tools menu.

Summary: Switching targets now reindexes/loads index in a blocking fashion
Description:
This started in the previous beta, and is present in the RC. Essentially it now takes a long time to swap build targets again.

First it tries to load the index, but it seems to always also (partially?) rebuild it, even if I just came from the other target. For my project, on a Mac Pro, it takes about 22 seconds to switch build targets, during which time AppCode naturally is non-responsive.

I can see why you need a different index since defines and such might differ, but why is it done in the foreground? Swapping between device and simulator is a relatively frequent thing in my daily development work.

Summary: Create Patch: create patch dialog resizes several time when displayed.
Cannot find source file for class in "test" folder of library project
Description:
I have a FlashBuilder Library project that I imported as a module. It has a src folder and a test folder (both of which contain code).

The first issue is that the import created "test" as a source folder.  That is incorrect, it's actually a unit test folder.  I modified the module settings, deleted "test" as a source folder and added it as a "test source" folder.

When I try to compile the project, I get the following error: [LibraryProject] could not find source for class TestRunner.

TestRunner is a class that exists immediately under the "test" test source folder.  It is not in a separate package.  Compiling the library should not try to include the test sources in the library as well.  

As a workaround, If I delete the test source folder then the project compiles OK.  Also, as an aside, even though I have a test source folder set, I don't see an option to run unit tests for the module.  Maybe I'm just missing it or it's not implemented yet...?

Summary: Add ability to clear Recent Patterns list
Code completion and code navigation not working in Rubmine
Description:
Per Serge's suggestion in [a forum discussion|http://devnet.jetbrains.net/thread/313101], I'm logging this as a ticket with my full project attached. I tried to reproduce this in a small, made-up project and it didn't happen.

I am seeing two problems which I'm not sure are related.

Problem 1: "Find usages" is producing weird results. If I right-click on a method definition and do "Find Usages" (which should find 6 usages, based on a free text search), it sometimes returns "no usages" and sometimes finds two usages. It's especially troubling that the results don't stay the same.

Problem 2: Ctrl-click navigation of code is mostly failing to navigate my code. Occasionally it will, but mostly it'll find the earliest use of a method in a given script, rather than navigating to the source definition of a method. This works occasionally but mostly doesn't.

Since both of these problems are intermittent, I was thinking maybe they have the same cause and perhaps same solution.

I'm using RubyMine 3.2.4 on Windows 7 (64 bit) with Ruby 1.9.1

Summary: Parameter name completion for Groovy DSL support
Description:
I take advantages of the Groovy DSL support (as described in http://jetbrains.dzone.com/articles/custom-groovy-dsl-support), but I'm badly missing one feature. Namely, to be able to auto-complete parameter names.

In Groovy, one often defines a method like foo(Map,Closure) and then invoke it like foo(abc:1, def:2) { ... }. And it'd be mighty handy to be able to provide auto-completion for "abc" and "def" in this case. This pattern shows up in the markup builder, node builder, and ant builder. The *.gdsl files use this themselves to define method, property, and so on.

Summary: Console folding: additional patterns
Description:
Here's my current list of folding options. The general idea is to still be able to tell what was going on in a stack trace (what are the major levels of indirection) but not to be bothered with all those internal helpers.

Feel free to add to the defaults whatever you deem appropriate...

Summary: Add Files/Frameworks/* Menu: place right after 'New->' menu
Create folder in Xcode view do not appear
Description:
In project dockable panel, using the Xcode view, it is possible to create a folder.
The problem is that it doesn't create a group for that folder so the new folder do not appear unless I switch to file view. This is disturbing because the first time I thought the folder was not created. I think creating a folder should suggest to create a group at the same time.

Summary: Unused test methods
Description:
gh-unit (https://github.com/gabriel/gh-unit) is a framework for unit tests which I use a lot. AppCode always displayed a lot of warnings in the tests, but the latest beta2 started to show errors in a project which compiles and runs fine.
See the attached project and the test class "TestTheTest". The errors are spotted easily, and at least the warning that the class and some methods are unused are not correct.

Summary: Can't complete the local variable of type void*
missing auto-complete for members of property when .h file is not included
Description:
NOTE: Please edit the summary, after reading this to something more meaningful :)

I've attached 2 classes: Foo and Bar.
Foo has a property from type Bar, but in Foo.h there is only a @class Bar and not an #import Bar.h .

Trying to access Bar's members using any type of auto-complete results a "No suggestion" popup (see attached screenshot).
The solution is to:
1. Import manually Bar.h in Foo.h
2. OR Import manually Bar.h where Foo is used.
3. OR Type a fake function name on the bar property, wait for couple of secs so the import suggestion will appear.

IMHO, An auto-import of Bar.h to the current file should occur once the bar property is accessed.

with new/class action it is impossible to create class with duplicated name; in xcode this is also forbidden

Summary: Rename a non-empty directory doesn't take effect until expanding the directory
Description:
''Build 109.38''

Open Files View.
Create a directory ''foo''.
Put some content to ''foo'' (e.g. create a subdirectory).
Collapse ''foo''.
Rename ''foo'' to ''foo2''.

Result: name hasn't changed.
Expand ''foo'' - its name will change to ''foo2''.

The problem doesn't happen with groups.

Summary: Analysis becomes turned on in the files from the Items to Skip list after solution is closed
Description:
R# Options -> Code Inspections -> Settings.
Press "Edit Items to Skip" button and add a file. Open the file - R# analysis is off. Close solution and reopen it - analysis is on in the file that should be skipped.

Summary: Bulk svn annotate
Description: As part of a code review, I often take a set of files and do svn annotate on them.  Ideally I could choose a single commit from the "repository" tab of the "changes" view and say "svn annotate everything".  Less perfect, but still very awesome, would be the ability to multi-select files and say "svn annotate all these files".

Summary: External Sources page is "broken" if more than one context tabs are opened
Description:
Open R# Options -> Tools -> External Sources.
Press 'Moar' and select a context - the tab is opened. Return to Smart context options - None of radio button values is selected.

Summary: VB: MyBase keyword shouldn't be shown in completion of Shared methods
idea should allow to shelve even in detached HEAD
Good code is red, override toString is not allowed
Description: as3 error is shown "method inherited from object does not need override" when trying to override toString. Files with sample code are attached. When open SampleC.as file, error is shown, but compilation works good. If remove override specifier then code is green, but compilation doesn't work.

Summary: Agent upgrade may hung if too long path was used
Description: Upgrade process is started without process stdin stderr stream reader. This may lead upgrade process to hung if Java/OS buffer is full or if Upgrade process tries to log long message to console.

Summary: Agent service cannot be restarted under limited account
Description:
I need to run build agent service under limited account which has no administrative privileges.
- The account is a member of *Users* group
- It has *Modify* permissions on TeamCity directory
- has *Logon as a service* user right
- has *Full control* permissions on *TCBuildAgent* service

The service is started successfully, connects to the server, downloads plugins, but fails to stop itself for upgrade:

> [2011-05-02 14:04:48,605]   INFO - r.agent.upgrade.UpgradeRunBase - Run command line (arguments separated with '|'): cmd.exe|/c|C:\TeamCity\buildAgent\bin\service.stop.bat| (at C:\TeamCity\buildAgent\bin)
> [2011-05-02 14:04:49,693]   INFO - .agent.run.ProcessOutputLogger -  
> [2011-05-02 14:04:49,696]   INFO - .agent.run.ProcessOutputLogger - C:\TeamCity\buildAgent\bin>..\launcher\bin\TeamCityAgentService-windows-x86-32.exe -p ../conf/wrapper.conf  
> [2011-05-02 14:04:50,308]   INFO - .agent.run.ProcessOutputLogger - wrapper  | OpenSCManager failed - Access is denied. (0x5)

Launching *service.stop.bat* manually causes the same error. But *sc stop TCBuildAgent* command does work correctly.

Also, when the service is started, my account does not have permissions in security token of *TeamCityAgentService-windows-x86-32.exe*, but have them in tokens of child *java.exe* processes.

It seems launcher performs some additional calls to SCM that limited account has no permissions for.

As workaround I modified *service.stop.bat* and *service.start.bat* files to use *sc.exe*.

Summary: SQL: PostgreSQL: Throwable at PsiElementBase.notNullChild() on attempt in CREATE OPERATOR for containment
Description:
Create .sql file with PostgreSQL dialect.
Paste there the following valid code:
{code}
CREATE OPERATOR <@ (
LEFTARG = _int4,
RIGHTARG = _int4,
PROCEDURE = _int_contained,
RESTRICT = contsel,
JOIN = contjoinsel
);
{code}
(It's from PostgreSQL installation.)
Regarding validity see http://www.postgresql.org/docs/9.1/interactive/sql-createoperator.html
IDEA cannot complete analysis and throws exceptions.

See also IDEA-75711.
110.162.

Summary: Can't delete user: error messages should be more friendly.
Description:
When I try to delete an user I get the following error message:

Can't remove [User: id = 22-0[up-to-date] (RemovedSaved)] because there're the following incoming links: 1: Project: id = 38-0[up-to-date] (Saved).leader 2: Project: id = 38-1[up-to-date] (Saved).createdBy

Since this user was a project leader I removed the association, however I still have the an error, this time a litle different:

Can't remove [User: id = 22-0[up-to-date] (RemovedSaved)] because there're the following incoming links: 1: Project: id = 38-1[up-to-date] (Saved).createdBy

Comparing error messages seems that the reason is that it was the user that created some of the projects.

Messages should be more friendly in such cases.

I did not marked this as a bug since I am not sure if this is a wrong behavior, despite de fact that I do not find any reason for not deleting this user.

Unable to find path of shared javascript / css elements, where these elements reside in a different project.
Description:
I have one website project that contains common jQuery framework files.  

I have a second project that contains my ASP.net application.

Both of these projects are in the same solution.

Now, if I reference one of the shared js files from an aspx page in my ASP.net application, ReSharper can't find it.

For example, my application lives in a virtual directory, called app, and the shared resources live in a directory called shared.  If you reference the shared resources like so:

<script src="/shared/js/jquery.js"></script>

Then ReSharper won't be able to find the resources.  I would expect that maybe it should look at what the Server configuration is for the ASP project, and see rather or not it really lives at the root path of a URL.  Alternatively, some way to map projects so that ReSharper can more intelligently find the related resources would be superb.  This effectively breaks all intellisense for ReSharper in regards to those files.

It can be not clear for the user (where the file is searched for?) and also can create a false impression that this is some TeamCity error, let's amend the message e.g. as follows:

An error occurred during collecting maven data: Could not file "pom.xml" in VCS

BTW, error style seems wrong (too condensed font)

Summary: Adjust namespaces and Silverlight 4
Description:
When I run the Reshaper -> Refactor -> Adjust Namespaces option in my Silverlight 4 project Resharper appends a x:Class attribute to the ResourceDictionary tag in my xaml theme files.  
When I re-compile and run my Silverlight app I get a "Invalid or malformed application: Check manifest" message.  This is caused by a XamlParseException xClassNotDerivedFromElement caused by the x:Class attribute added to the Xaml Theme file.  Deleting the attribute from the Theme xaml corrects the problem.

Summary: Provide documentation on config dialog
Visual Studio 2010 Crashes Repeatedly During Solution Analysis
Description:
With Team Foundation Server 2005 or 2008 in use, Visual Studio 2010 32bit on Windows XP SP3 (3Gb physical memory, 4Gb virtual memory) will repeatedly crash in solutions with complex XSD documents such as DAL OleDb/OracleClient/SQLClient connections including datatables and table adapters.

The workaround is that when loading the solution which has solution wide analysis enabled, when Team Foundation Server popups to say "Do you want to get the latest version of solution files?" I leave this screen open without clicking anything and ReSharper 6 will happily analyse the solution in the background and NEVER crashes this way, but if I get the latest solution files and then let ReSharper analyse the solution it will ALWAYS run out of memory or crash for another reason.

Can you please analyse what the difference between solution analysis is before and after the Team Foundation Server dialog is?


Thanks!

Summary: Wrong "Build agent distribution has changed on disk." in the logs
Description:
Sometimes the server gets messages like:
{quote}
[2011-09-09 18:21:26,040]   INFO - ins.files.ServerPluginUnpacker - Plugin was removed at path: /TeamCity/webapps/ROOT/WEB-INF/plugins/mercurial.zip. The change will become effective after TeamCity server restart.  

[2011-09-09 18:21:38,541]   INFO - e.impl.agent.PluginsLookupTask - Build agent distribution has changed on disk. 
{quote}

But there were no related disk modifications.

This might happen when there is "Too many open files" on Linux or, seems like on other IE errors.

Let's doublecheck and ensure that when there errors monitoring files:
- we do not consider the files missing and just do nothing
- the error is logged (with precautions not to fill the entire log. The message should probably be logged as WARN and stacktrace as DEBUG.

Let's ensure the issue is checked in all the relevant disk monitoring places.

Summary: Errors accessing buildAgent.zip by the server can result in all agents marked as "outdated"
Description:
When the server encounters errors reading agent distribution or agent plugins, it initiates agent upgrades as if there are no files with error present. This is wrong behavior (e.g. see TW-13552).

On encountering an error reading the files, server should:
- log the error details into the server log (only message, stacktrace in debug)
- do NOT initiate any upgrades, just ignore the "change" in files. initiate upgrade only when no errors occurred during agent distribution and plugins reading
- display a yellow warn in the web UI with the error details (like on not enough disk space error).

Details:

A server with an agent connected.

Summary: Illegal domain attribute ".tv.jetbrains.net" WARN in console while running idea
It is impossible to find how to hide coverage highlighting
Description:
I've ran coverage on a file. It became highlighted. Now I want to hide it.
* If my Mac wouldn't have a nice feature for searching throw the menu, I wouldn't find the dialog "Show Code Coverage Data", because the action is located under Tools, while "Run with Coverage" is located under "Run" menu and in the context menu. It is also not clear if "Show Code Coverage Data" would help user to clear highlighting.
* I would never find the way to hide highlighting from the file: LEFT clicking near line numbers and then pressing the cross in the popup without any title.  Thanks to a colleague who pointed me to that :)

I suggest to place "Hide Coverage Highlighting" action either in the standard context menu, or in the context menu invoked by clicking on the gutter (together with "Annotate", "Show line numbers" and other). The action should be invisible if the file is not highlighted with coverage report.

Summary: Replicate Eclipse-like behavior for Editor Tabs
Description:
1. Idea Editor always shows consecutive tabs regardless which ones were accessed more recently.
Assuming there is room for 5, it would be 1-5 or 3-7 or 6-10, etc. There is no quick and easy way to bring tab-1 and tab-10 into view at the same time. Of course tabs can be rearranged [only the visible ones!] but it's time consuming - especially when there are 15 tabs at a time.
In Eclipse jumping from any tab to another never hides the first one without the developer having to do anything for that.
2. The Ctrl+E view as more informative should replace the current Tab popup activated by pressing Tab row arrows.

Summary: "Concurrency annotation issues": support JSR 305 javax.annotation.concurrent
Description:
The inspections in the group "Concurrency annotation issues" only support annotations in "net.jcip.annotations".

Because JSR 305 is standard (javax.annotation.concurrent.*), please add support for it also.

Maybe similar to @Nullable/@Nonnull where we can specify our own annotations to use.

Description:

Irritating when going through a long list of changes to commit.

Summary: REST Client should have a link to Proxy settings
Description: Actually I am working on some RESTful web services but the network environment is not configured very well. I often hat change the Proxy settings. Is it possible to place a link to proxy settings from within the REST Client?

Summary: Add Company Nexus Repository
Description:
http://devnet.jetbrains.net/thread/313344

If I press Alt-Insert on a Maven pom file there is the opportunity to insert a repository template.
This has stuff like central, codehaus, java.net etc in it.

I want to add my company repository into this list.

It looks like the values are stored in 
{code}
${idea-install-dir}\plugins\maven\lib\maven.jar::org\jetbrains\idea\maven\dom\converters\repositories\repositories.xml
{code}
Obviously editing that file by hand is a a bit of a hassle and needs to be done every time I install a new version of IDEA.

There should be an easy way to add my company repository into this list.

On top of this, it would need to persist through upgrades of IDEA.

To make it really useful in a corporate setting, this info (and potentially other stuff) should be configurable to be pulled from some centralised place.
e.g. when I connect to the license server

If I use the syntax ${*} and remove the delimeters part of the conf all is right 
{code}
<plugin>
<groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>
<artifactId>maven-resources-plugin</artifactId>
<version>2.4.3</version>
<configuration>
<encoding>UTF-8</encoding>
<delimiters>

</configuration>
</plugin>

Summary: Performance issues with Type System rules
Description:
Currently, all type system rules as well as the NonTypesystemRules are executed "autoamtically" if something changes. For large models, this can be come a performance problem.

This could be solved by marking a rule as RUN_ON_CHANGE or RUN_ONLY_IN_CHECKER. 

Rules with RUN_ON_CHANGE are checked in realtime, just as now. RUN_ONLY_IN_CHECKER is only checked if the model checker is run by the user.

Summary: Problems to place caret using mouse, when error popup (on syntax error) appears in this place
Description:
It seems it's problem with popup position.

2. Move mouse to second line

Then popup will appear according to first position and then it will be impossible to place caret.

Windows 7, IDEA 110.137

Summary: set<node<>> and Set<SNode> etc. not assignment-compatible
Description:
A method DataFlow.getUnreachableNodes(program) returns Set<SNode>

We were trying to assign it to a variable types set<node<>> as in

   set<node<>> unreachableNodes = DataFlow.getUnreachableNodes(program);

However, this is not assignment-compatible.

Summary: Property Picker does not display without adding Build Properties and Environment Variables
Description:
When using a Build Step such as FxCop, the Property Picker for the Build Step does not appear to allow one to pick %system.FxCopRoot% even though the property is internally defined.  Instead, one must manually add at least one build property or environment variable to the build configuration before the Property Picker displays.

For Build Steps such as FxCop, the Property Picker should be available for the Build Step regardless of whether or not there are existing Build Properties or Environment variables currently defined.

Summary: FxCop runner results page will not show source code line number or open in IDE
Description:
I am having a problem with the FxCop results not actually showing the line number for errors.  It is running successfully, but each error has a line number of zero and will not open the source in the IDE when it is linked to.  I have attached a screenshot.

I have set it up to run after my Solution is built and tested.  It takes the artifacts from the /bin/Release folder and unzips them before running.  Again there is no problem running the build.  Please let me know if there is any more information I can provide you on this issue.

Summary: Detect FxCop 10.0 (from Windows SDK)
Problem setting custom ruleset for fxcop (vs2010)
Description: I have a custom ruleset for fxCop in vs2010 (it's included in the 2010 installation) that I am able to run in an msbuild script with no problem, but trying to get the fxCop runner to work with it has failed me. I tried adding it to the "extra parameters", but I can't get parameter expansion to work correctly (since it requires the rules directory to be specified. It's in a path with spaces (I can't help that because it's in program files), but if I include spaces around the parameter (like /r:"%env.fxCopPath%/Rules") every variation on that results in parameter errors. Without quotes it treats each space in the parameter like another parameter, but with quotes it never seems to expand correctly. To properly use FxCop, we really need to be able to specify rulesets (/rs:+/-/=) and paths to rule assemblies and folders (/r:)

Summary: FxCop: Incorrect handling of doublequotes in "Additional FxCopCmd options"
Description:
from http://www.jetbrains.net/devnet/thread/282122?tstart=0

The "Additional FxCopCmd options" textbox incorrectly handles doublequotes. To replicate:


In the FxCop runner configuration, enter the following into the "Additional FxCopCmd options" textbox: /d:References1 /d:References2

Save and run the build configuration.

Verify (via the Build Log) that fxcopcmd was executed with the correct arguments.

In the FxCop runner configuration, change /d:References1 to /d:"My References".

Save and run the build configuration.

Check the Build Log again.


This time you will see that instead of the arguments looking like

/d:"My References" /d:References2

... you will see:

"/d:"My References"" /d:References2

(Note the extraneous doublequotes around the first parameter.)

Summary: Import existing inspection xml report into FXCop runner
Description: Hi, in recent versions some releases of Visual Studio have built-in support for code inspection which is carried out using FXCop which ships with VS itself. It would be useful to employ the TC FXCop runner to parse existing inspection reports generated during compilation of the VS solution instead of having to run FXCop once again.

- Existing methods of objects as non-existing methods

Summary: "check" keyword not shown for :==: operator
Description:
In the type system rules, rules that use the :<=: operator use the word "check" as part of the rule text if the check-only flag is set. Example:
  
   check( typeof( var.init ) :<=: typeof( var.type ) )

However, if we use the :==: operator instead of :<=:, the "check" keyword is not shown. This is confusing.

Summary: Add support for code contracts
Description:
It would be nice if R# had some quick fixes and refactorings that makes working with code contracts easier.

I'd like to see the following features:

1) "Generate contract class for interface" refactoring
Code Contracts for interfaces have to be placed in an abstract class, as the interface does not have method bodies where the contract calls could be placed. It would be nice if R# could generate such a class for me.

2) "Move contract to contract class" quick fix
Sometimes I forget to place the contracts of a method in the contract class, and place them in the class that implements the interface instead. ReSharper should warn me about that and offer to move the contracts to the contract class. It could also create the contract class if it does not exist yet.

3) "Extract Interface" refactoring should generate a contract class if the methods that are extracted to an interface contain code contracts.

Summary: 'Go to' a NIB file without having the current project opened in Xcode results in missing images and references in Interface Builder
Description:
1. Don't run Xcode
2. Use 'Go to File' to open a NIB file 
3. Xcode will launch the file and displays it by itself. All images defined in the NIB file show up as '?'.

I need to close the NIB file, open the current project in Xcode, then go back to AppCode and use 'Go to File' again to have it opened correctly.

Summary: Pressing 'enter' after opening '{' adds an extra closing '}' despite one already exists
Is it possible to return some metrics on a filter result rather than the full dump of the issues?
Description:
Hi,
Using our current isue tracker (fortress) we display a dashboard of metrics in mediawiki.  There are many advantages to embedding dynamic data from the issuetracker within wiki articles, and it is a cornerstone of our process.  It works very well, and I need to replicate this with youtrack as the back end.

Here is an example of a wiki page displaying some dynamic data.  Each time the page is rendered, it connects to fortress, and extracts the information.

I guess I could do this with the current REST API, but it would be more efficient if YT had a method to return the filter result ''count'' rather than the actual records.  This becomes important if you have hundreds or thousands of issues, as your max limit starts to become a problem, and the whole thing slows down to a crawl.

specifically, I would like;
* A method to return the '''count''' from a a filter query
* The '''sum''' of a a ''numeric field'' (e.g. time estimates) from a filter query

!screenshot1.png!

FYI, here are the actual issues in a wiki article.  you can see the duration at the bottom of the table.  I have noted that YT is a fair bit slower than fortress (SQLserver) at extracting records from its DB, but I need to make some more detailed tests before I formally report this.

!screenshot2.png!

The "fake project" is located in the PhpStorm project root." Most frameworks tools operate with project, so, your first command in new project should be "create initial project".

*# or /app/console file in Symfony2

I also attached a snapshot of what the audit logs showed when teamcity was in a bad state.

Thanks,
Jay

Summary: Undo undoes too much when deleting stuff with IdeaVIM
Description:
There's a bug in the way IdeaVIM undoes changes.

Start with the following string, "Use the video's ID, not the playlist entry ID."
Place your cursor right before the "'".
Hit "de" to delete the "'s".
Type "lll" to move the cursor to ",".
Type "x" to delete the ",".
Type "u" to undo the change.

It should only undo the comma deletion, but it actually undoes both deletions.  You should have to hit "u" two times in order to undo both deletions.

I think timing is actually a factor, so you may have to do it a few times in order to do it quickly.

Summary: Undo "u" sometimes undoes many more items than the last edit
Description: Today I've twice had ideavim undo over 5 minutes of work with a single "u" press.  It's cascading too far back into the edits instead of undoing simply the last edit as VIm would do.

Summary: UI bug on Internet Explorer 9
Description:
User reports:

{quote}
# Launch http://youtrack.jetbrains.net/issues on IE 9
# Using the scrollbar, scroll down on the page
# Now, click on one of the issues near the bottom
# Notice how YouTrack “jumps” back to the top of the page INSTEAD OF showing the details of drilling into the issue that you just clicked on.

This “jumping” behavior causes a lot of erroneous clicks.  This UI bug seems to happen on IE only.  Hope you can fix it as it affects a lot of our users.
{quote}

Summary: Login form: Text about JIRA account always displayed, even if no JIRA integration configured.
Description:
On the login (and Register New User Account form) we always show text "Do you have JIRA account at ... You can use it log in" Even if no Jira integration specified. So, If no Jira server specified the phrase is at least confusing. Let alone it sounds like "Do you have JIRA account at." 
I guess we should show this message only if Jira integration is enabled.

Summary: More fine grained role definition
Description:
We're using YouTrack not only for software but also for hardware related issues. Therefor we implemented some kind of a review panel which has to review all issues first and assign them to the team leaders. These teamleaders now has to assign the issues to their team members.
I was asked by the management if it would be possible to split the "Update Issue Private Fields" in a more fine grained way. My colleagues would like to enable/disable especially "Assign issue to user" and "Set priority" separately.

Summary: Prohibit guest user from changing issues
Description:
Guest user changed an issue, see screenshot attached.
This happened on the youtrack.jb.com about 20 times already.

Please make sure this will not happen again. If it happens on our server it also can happen in the user's installations, so this SHOULD be handled.

I am ready to participate in discussion for the necessary measures.

Summary: Make 'fixed in XXX' command actually close the issue as fixed, and do not set 'Fix for XXX' instead
Description:
It is quite annoying to write command such as' fixed fixed in XXX'.
What I mean by 'fixed in XXX' command is 'mark the issue as fixed and set fix version to XXX'.
At the moment YouTrack confusingly understand 'fixed in XXX' as 'if issue is open, set fix for to XXX, otherwise set fix version to XXX'

Summary: Recursive execution of workflow rules does not consider issue project
Description:
Suppose you have:
Issue I1 belonging to Project P1
Issue I2 belonging to Project P2
I1 relates to I2
Workflow Rule WFR attached only to P1, not P2

A change in I1 triggers WFR, which in turn changes I2 so that it meets Guard criteria from WFR.
Expected: the rule is not applied to I2.
Actual: the rule is applied to I1.

Summary: Duplicates: Aggregate Data
Description:
Our JIRA experience indicates that it's not unusual to have tens of duplicates for a large number of issues (the stack traces are different and they wouldn't auto-merge when submitting).

When it's time to work on such an issue, it's 
impossible to accumulate all of the user feedback (possible comments, steps to repro, etc) from all of the duplicates in a reasonable amount of time.

For such issues, when they're being closed as duplicates, their comments, votes, watchers, attachments, etc should be reattached to the duplicates-root issue.

Summary: Wrong comment attachment file visibility group
Description:
Steps:
# set visibility group A to comment
# attach file to comment, set attachment visibility group to B
# submit comment

Expects that attachment would have visibility group B.
Result: attachment has visibility group A.

Summary: Support "contains" for collections
Create tag presentation with additional info. Special event-dependent type of tags
Description:
We use "waiting for reply" tag, this is just shared tag to mark issues with unanswered questions to users project-wide.

It generally works to make work easier, but I thought we could create specific type of tags:
when some event (in this case, comment from bug creator or any user) occurs, tag could be displayed with some additional mark, like:

waiting for reply (answered?)

Maybe this situation can be handled in some other way, but it would be indeed very useful, since we are not using interaction model where bugs are assigned to the creator when the question is asked.

Description: Now counter on Linked Issues update more quickly

Summary: Initial state vs default /selected values
Description:
I'm surprised that default or user selected values are ignored when a workflow is employed (assumes I have a workflow for the field e.g. Type)

When creating an issue, if I have a default value for a field, or if I explicitly selected a value, it is ignored and overidden by the initial state of the workflow. 

If the initial state takes precedence it should not be possible to select an alternate value when creating the issue. I'd prefer that if a user has selected a value then the issue should enter the workflow at that point and the workflow designer should ensure that on entry to the state all prerequisites are met and/or appropriate state is set.

Summary: Disable Run button if watched project cannot be run by some reason and is queued .
Description:
Let's consider the situation when some build configuration does not have compatible agent at the moment or all agents are busy at the moment.
Run the build configuration from TeamCity Watched Projects view.

It is queued but no notitification for user in IDE is dispalyed. Moreover, since Run button is enabled user can press it many times (build configurations are not run and are not queued any more).

Disable Run button for queued build configurations.

Also user notification for queued buidls would be useful in IDE.
Some text like #1.1.100 Added to Build Queue ideally with the link to Build queue page in Web.

Summary: "Create from usages" is disabled outside of a class
Intentions for property - remove '... for property Foo' text from intention names to make the choices more clear
Description:
Currently it is very hard to read the options in the popup because of too much text.
The better options are:

----------------------
Synthesize property
Add accessor methods
Enable 'read' attribute
....
Make @dynamic
----------------------

and remove Safe delete option since we have special action for it - Once you learn the shortcut, you will never use intention to safe delete (it is unexpected to see it here)

Summary: mode change keys not always recognized
Description:
Sometimes mode change keys (i.e. ESC in insert mode, a,A,i, etc. in command mode) have no effect. Repeatedly pressing them (or just waiting and trying again?) resolves issue. But very annoying because a keyboard stream of fooESCwwabar ends up in the code as foowwabar rather than foo<move cursor>bar.

Perhaps related to IntelliJ as a whole being unresponsive due to e.g. Scala plug-in burning cycles?

Summary: ESC doesn't always register
Description:
Using RM 3.2.2 and IdeaVIM 0.16.60 I am experiencing ESC not working when trying to exit insert mode. Hitting it several times over and over still doesn't make it work although it doesn't happen every time.

I have noticed that hitting Backspace followed by ESC will sometimes make it properly exit the mode, however then of course the last character is deleted.

Summary: Tests are all red when run with dotCover
Description:
The dotCover installation on my developer pc has stopped working. Running any test will result in one of two exceptions.

1. For test methods without any setup:
 System.MissingMethodException : Method not found: 'Void System.Runtime.Versioning.TargetFrameworkAttribute.JetBrains_Profiler_Core_Instrumentation_Begin(UIntPtr ByRef)'.

2. If a test is preceded by setup using, for example, "TestFixtureSetup":
TestFixtureSetUp failed in ApiServiceInstanceProviderTestsWithIoc
-- Exception doesn't have a stack trace -- 

I suspect #2 is actually the same problem as #1 but it's difficult to say without any stacktrace.
The tests all run green using the Resharper test-runner and on our build-server using NUnit console runner.

Visual Studio 2010 SP1

Summary: Automatically create build configurations for every new git branch
Description:
from http://www.jetbrains.net/devnet/message/5235473

aarnott:
I have a branch for every minor version of the project, and then a few feature branches that come and go as needed, and I'd like build configurations for all of these.  So for example, I have "master" for the next big thing, and then maintenance branches for "v2.5", "v2.4", "v2.3", etc.  In each of these branches I have tags for each revision, such as v2.5.4.  Feel free to visit http://github.com/AArnott/dotnetopenid/ if you want to see the branches as I use them directly.  So right now I have about a dozen branches I would want to build.  Then I have a few other branches that don't contain source code, or whose source base is so old the build configuration would have to be adjusted for.

> Do you think of automatic build configuration creation for every new branch or some other approach?


Yes.  As soon as a branch is created on the repository that TeamCity pulls from, I'd like a build configuration to be automatically created based on some template configuration.  After these configurations are created, I may need to customize them and/or delete them and they should stay altered/deleted, but by far the most common case would be a build for every new branch.

Summary: dotCover fails on .NET 4.0 assemblies

Sorry for the very generic summary, will update it once the problem can be limited to a tighter scope.

I'm trying to use dotCover to determine test coverage on a .NET 4.0 class library. Because I wanted a homogeneous .NET 4.0 environment, I'm running the unit tests with a custom .NET 4.0 build of NUnit (that shouldn't bother dotCover as it's not a modified NUnit but a general purpose coverage engine where NUnit just happens to be another assembly being analyzed).

I've set nunit-console-x86.exe as the target executable and my assembly as the target arguments. Summary: dotCover affects deployment parameters specified in local test settings of MSTest
Description:
feedback from Roger Dawson:
"I have some unit tests that depend on some test data contained in a 'testdata' folder. I have modified my local test settings so that my test data is deployed to the test output directory (VS2010 > Test > Edit Test Settings > Local > Deployment -> Enable Deployment). This works fine and I end up with my testdata folder being copied to the TestResults\<User@Machine Date Time>\Out folder. This folder is at the root of my solution folder.

However, when I run tests using dotcover the TestResults folder is placed within the bin\debug folder of the test project. My deployment files are not copied across to this new location either.

Therefore my question is how do I get my deployment items to copy to the relocated TestResults folder or is there a way of getting dotcover to use the traditional ms unit test location for the TestResults folder (i.e. at the root of the solution folder and not the bin\debug folder for the test project)."

Description:

User is supposed to click on "syntax help", which has issues:
- it's non standard approach through TeamCity UI
- user cannot see helper text and the content of the text area
- the text displayed there is not adjusted properly to the artifact dependency dialog (probably copy-pasted from checkout rules)

Let's:
1. Add standard-styled gray helper text under the text area:
{quote}
Lines in the form BuildArtifactsPattern[=>TargetAgentDirectory]
{quote}

2. Add our standard help link icon which will
a) open a popup with longer helper text (can discuss the content), or
b) open TeamCity online help with appropriate anchor

3. remove "syntax help" link

Summary: Need run configuration to debug remote Flash Player
Suppress unused parameters when method annotated with X
Bookmarks
Description:
Copied from the forum http://devnet.jetbrains.net/message/5302931#5302931


You seem to have done a bit of rework on the Bookmark feature in AppCode 108.197.
 
However, it misbehaves in a number of ways.
 
Sometimes when a bookmark is added, the bookmark is places before the filename in the project view, and the filename is written in the Courier font. But the file extension is chopped of (see bookmark 2 of attached screenshot).
The bookmark+courier formatting of filenames is only applied occasionally - in my screenshot, eg. MenuOrderViewController+TableMethods.m holds bookmark 3, but this isn't reflected in the project view.
When I remove a bookmark from the Command+F3 dialog (as the case is with bookmark 6 in my screenshot), the bookmark is removed from the bookmark list, but it appears to still be present in the sourcecode (bookmark 6 is shown just above the bookmarks list).
The bookmark 6 eventually disappeared from the sourcecode listing view as well, after I had clicked to edit the file. However, not only did bookmark 6 disappear, also the other bookmarks (1-3) disappeared from the sourcecode listings. The bookmarks 1-3 were still active though, but the litte bookmark marker was not shown next to the sourcecode.

Summary: Rename without Refactor
Description:
Renaming a file through a refactor is usually not desired for us.

For example, if we rename a view file from show.html.erb to old_show.html.erb because we are migrating to a different templating system, the refactor will also change the action name, before/after filters, etc.

In the refactoring preview, we only select to change the file name, but RubyMine will still change everything mentioning that file.

This introduces more bugs because it's changing parts of the code that we don't want to be changed. Our controller action changes to 'old_show' so our new 'show.html.haml' (for example) is not referenced properly nor are our before/after filters.

All I want to do is rename a file. No refactoring is required. Can you please implement a simple 'Rename file' function?

import to Astella - FACET_COMPILE_OUTPUT_PATH option is ignored, resultant build configuration has the output folder taken from the compile out path of the facet containing module

Summary: Resharper 6 performance issue when editing Razor views
Description:
I upgraded to Resharper 6 and I've noticed some serious performance issues in Visual Studio when editing Razor view templates. Typing is delayed significantly even when editing text that isn't contained in a razor or html tag and intellisense takes a noticeable amount of time to appear. The delay on keyboard input makes editing razor views very difficult. I've cleared the cache from the Resharper Options menu but it didn't help at all. 

I uploaded a DotTrace performance file to the JetBrains FTP server. The filename is RazorViewPerformanceSnapshot.zip

Thank you.

Description:
1. If build configuration (BC) with this main class exists
  1.1. If run configuration based on such BC exists - launch it
  1.2. If several run configurations exist - show popup to choose which to launch
2. If several BCs with this main class exist - allow to choose which one is desired to be launched; launch existing run configuration based on selected BC or create missing run configuration
3. If none BC exist with this main class - suggest to create one, then create run configuration and launch it.

Summary: Visual representation of implicit conversions and implicit parameters usage
Display which implicit conversion was used
Description:
IntelliJ already highlights places where implicit conversion is used, e.g.:

{code:scala}BigDecimal(5) + 3{code}

In the code above "{{3}}" is softly underlined to indicate that implicit conversion takes places. This is a wonderful feature, however I would appreciate if IntelliJ could also show the actual conversion ({{scala.math.BigDecimal#int2bigDecimal}}) in this case) using popup or some shortcut.

Shouldn't be hard since this information must be already available somewhere in the plugin.

Summary: File Colors: some default scopes are incorrect, scopes management is allowed but doesn't work properly
Description:
109.40
it seems that the scopes are removed from appcode - there is no special setting for them, and it is impossible to save the local scope.
However the scopes management and scopes themselves are available in FileColors settings.

The Test default scope doesn't work - no classes are recognized as test ones; the custom scopes created via Manage Scopes also don't work.

Summary: Syntax highlighting apparently not using header search paths to find  declarations for a prebuilt static library
Description:
I've attached a project showing the issue. It refers to a static library in a location outside of the project.
The path to the library's headers is specified in the HEADER_SEARCH_PATHS build setting (hardcoded in the build settings for simplicity here). The headers are clearly found by the build system, as everything builds OK, and syntax highlighting and completion work in Xcode.
But in Appcode (beta 3), symbols defined in the library's headers show as red, and there's no completion (see UserHeaderTestTests.m).

I initially thought this might be the same  issue as http://youtrack.jetbrains.net/issue/OC-1018, but I realise now that was referring to as-yet unbuilt static lib projects. This is slightly different, in that the static lib is pre-built.

Summary: Suppressing spell checking
Description:
I am a Japanese intelliJ user.

We Japanese have a problem about spell checking.
We usually write comments in Japanese, but intelliJ assumes them as TYPO .

Adding Japanese dictionary does not solve the problem,
because, in Japanese, it is very difficult to identify separation of word
without considering meaning of the sentence.

Most of our comments are underwaved, so they are hard to see.
(To avoid this, I use very thin color to TYPO.)

I would like option suppressing spell checking to characters except alphabetic characters. 
This improvement will help not only Japanese, but also Chinese developers.
Please consider my proposal.

Summary: Change style of notifications in coverage results tab in test runner
Description: See how notifications are made in ReSharper (e.g. empty Find Results window)

Summary: Code formatter always adds blank line after last class declaration
UTR client controller: serialization of the error messages
Add goto Data flow statement that created this node in dataflow graph
Description: When using the data flow graph it is not easily visible where a certain node in the data flow graph originates from. It would be great to have a possibility to jump to the respective element in the dataflow editor that created this node

Summary: Size of popup shown on Ctrl + Alt + K (tests using code) should be calculated in a similar way to Ctrl + Alt + F7 (usages) pop-up in R#
Description: The problem is that window is too small(screenshot1.png), and even when I resize it - it becomes small next time #fail. In R# it is implemented in a much nicer way (screenshot2.png).

Summary: Suspending dotCover and resuming it in special moment makes Coverage tab of unit test runner disappear
Description:
1. suspend dotCover
2. relaunch Studio (to make 'Coverage results' tab disappear from Unit Test Sessions window)
3. open solution with tests, open any test file
4. select ReSharper -> Unit Tests -> Run Unit Tests - tests are run
5. resume dotCover (without closing UTS window!)
6. in UTS window, select a test and click 'Cover Selected Tests' - 'results' panel stayes blank, there's no coverage tab to see the snapshot (see attached pic).
Cured by relaunching VS.

Summary: Menu items "ReSharper->Unit Tests->Cover Unit Test / Cover All Tests from Solution" should be disabled when no solution is loaded
Description: In VS 2010 these items are always enabled.

Summary: Add subscription period to the dotCover license info
Problems with UpdateInfo serialization
Tests methods that use TestCaseSource NUnit Attribute do not properly run or show coverage
Description: Code that is executed by the various test inputs yieled by a TestCaseSource attribute do not cover properly. They do run properly when run by Resharper with Run/Debug Unit Tests, but dotCover does not cover them.

Summary: Good code red when using Spring's JaxWsPortProxyFactoryBean
Description:
I have bean defined in XML:
<bean id="offerCalculatorWsClient" class="org.springframework.remoting.jaxws.JaxWsPortProxyFactoryBean">
        <property name="serviceInterface" value="my.company.CalculationService"/>
        <property name="wsdlDocumentUrl" value="classpath:META-INF/offercalculator.wsdl" />
        <property name="namespaceUri" value="http://www.mycompany.com/1.0/" />
        <property name="serviceName" value="CalculationService" />
        <property name="portName" value="CalculationServicePort" />
        <property name="endpointAddress" value="${endpoint.url}" />
	</bean>

Then in another class I use annotations to inject that bean to code

@Autowired
my.company.CalculationService calculationService;

In this case it highlights calculationService in red with error "No beans of 'CalculationService' type found". Using code this way is valid as CalculationService interface is in Spring context. Tested the code by deploying my application and even I have unit test that starts the spring context and I can verify that injecting is done correctly.

Summary: Code formatter: indent empty comment lines equal to previous line
Code formatter: indent empty lines equal to previous line
false syntax error issues with next line continuation
Description:
With the following Rspec file:
{code lang=ruby}
require "spec_helper"

describe "weird condition" do
  it "should do something" do
    "1".should match \
      /1/
  end
end
{code}

We are seeing an error highlight after the second back slash. The syntax error given is "Expected: expression"

This following Rspec is actually valid Ruby and runnable without any syntax errors.

Summary: "Introduce constant" generates invalid code structure
Description:
RM-110.135
1. Code sample
{code}
class Foo
  def meth
    if true
      puts "introduce me as a constant"
    end
  end
end
{code}

In this case the constant stays under "if" which is incorrect

Summary: Export to CSV date is not in Excel readable form
Description:
When I export issues to CSV I get the date field as:

Thursday, October 20, 2011 9:20:49 AM CEST

Excel does not see this as a date, therefore I cannot sort on date.

Recommend that YouTrack uses 'Region and Language' settings and 'Long time and 'Long Date' formats (no comma separators in the date time field)

based on my setting the example above would be:

-20/10/2011 09:20:49
viewed by our company in Houston
-20/10/2011 02:20:49

TeamCity should not follow symbolic links when deleting files on agent (checkout directories and .old) - Linux
Description:
I'm running TeamCity 5.1 EAP (build 13130) on a Debian etch Linux server.

Our build process makes use of symbolic links in several places and it seems like TeamCity is having a hard time dealing with this. The project in question is built in a Linux environment and has links from within the checkout directory to outside the checkout directory. Our current build process depends on the semantics of 'rm -rf' when removing files, which is to remove the link instead of following the link. TeamCity, on the other hand, tries to follow the link and ends up either removing more than it should or failing to remove because it's stumbling into root-owned files.

I have 'Clean all files before build' checked in my VCS settings. I haven't completely tracked it down, but I think this is causing problems. We have a set of files that live outside the checkout directories and are shared among all checkout directories. We have symbolic links from within the checkout directory to the shared files. When TeamCity cleans the checkout directory, I think it is spidering into these shared files and removing them.

Also, when I check the error.log of the build agent I see a bunch of lines like:

[2010-03-11 17:02:42,368]   WARN - ctories.CleanupRegistryCleaner - Failed to remove file /home/venkman/TeamCity/buildAgent/work/.old/623da589b52cdcdd_98/lib/include/native/lastlog.h

This is because we've got a link from inside the checkout directory to /usr/include whose files are all owned by root. Since we're running the build as a non-root user, TeamCity can't remove these files. This leaves behind a bunch of directories in .old that TeamCity isn't able to remove. The larger problem here is that it shouldn't even be trying to remove these files.

I'm seeing lots of old checkout directories piling up in buildAgent/work/.old. I don't know if that's because of this problem, or if that's just normal behavior.

At this point I've turned off 'Clean all files before build' and am manually removing directories from .old. Things seem to be working, but I'm wondering if there might be other issues caused by symbolic links (like removing a build configuration, for example). And I'd like to be able to use the 'Clean all files before build' option.

Summary: Support adding playerglobal.swc for new Flash Player support
Description:
Steps:
1. Create build configuration with Flex SDK 4.5.1, targetplayer 10.2 (the only available in default SDK installation)
2. Download playerglobal.swc for Flash Player 11, save it to <Flex SDK>/frameworks/libs/player/11/
3. Configure build configuration to use target player 11 (it becomes available in respective combobox)
4. Try to compile - failure, because new playerglobal.swc does not appear in Astalla's internal root model.

Description:
Add information about:

*self execution time
*cumulative execution time

Summary: Statistics on Changes per build
Description: I would like to recommend a statistics on "changes per build". For us this is a relevant metric on our way to continuous delivery. Our goal is to bring this value to 1. You should have all values availible within the teamcity server, I just could not find a way, how to create a statistics chart for this metric.

Summary: Do not display Navigation Bar on detached editor windows
Description: This looks exessive. Status Bar could be also simplified for this (I mean memory indicator, notifications, progress removed - all that staff that is duplicated in main frame)

Summary: Warning about "No constructor function" must be disabled by default (according to Flash Builder and common sense)
Description:
I don't know any real reason to enable it by default.  Flash Builder — disabled by default. 

My suggestion — copy all warn* from flex sdk flex config and override default compiler configuration.

Summary: CPU profiling doesn't work properly with recursive functions
Description:
Steps to reproduce:

1) Start profiling attached application
2) Start CPU profiling
3) Click button
4) Stop CPU profiling
5) Observe Hotspots tab

Expected result: same execution time of runClickHandler and fib methods.

Actual result: execution time of fib method much greater than execution time of runClickHandler method.

Summary: Wrong position of the command window in google chrome
Description:
When I start typing with the focus on the issue-list the command-window pops up as it should but at the wrong position - see the screenshot which shows the whole display-width. I'm using a resolution of 1920x1200. I've only seen this with google-chrome v13.

When I open an issue and go back to the issue-list it works.

YouTrack is the start-page in the browser - maybe this is an initialisation problem.

Summary: "Mark file as" right-click menu
Description:
When you right-click a directory in your module, you have the option to "Mark Directory As" and select an option.

Similarly, it would be great if I could right-click a .swc in my module and "Mark File As" module library. This would save the many steps of opening the module settings/dependencies/select module/navigate to modules. (I know other Flex IDEs have this feature)

Summary: PhpStorm change file permissions after save.
Description:
Step for reproduce
1. check file permissions before open in editor:
$ ls -l default.php 
-rw-rw-r-- 1 miracle users 2608 Sep 15 11:53 default.php

2. Open,  edit and save

3. Check permissions again:
$ ls -l default.php 
-rw-rw---- 1 miracle users 2608 Oct 20 13:19 default.php


I can't find any visible settings such as "umask", "default file permission" or "remove access for other after save"

Summary: Wrong php syntax error inside SQL string
Description:
This example doesn't give me any completion after the '$' inside the string, then underlines it as if it's a syntax error - even though it does work fine.

<?php

$o['field'] = 1;

$sql = "select things from atable where field = {$o['field']}";

?>


Also, when I try to edit this sql fragment separately, what I get is :

select things from atable where  field = __o__field___

...and it messes everything up.

Summary: Wrap with trans tag: provide navigation to msgid_plural for string with plural part of blocktrans tag
Debugger: Variables View in Debugger collapses when stepping
Description:
Would it be possible to keep the Variables view in the same state between code steps?  I often drill down into objects to see their field values.  When I step, I have to drill down into the objects again to see the new values.  An added bonus would be to show which values have changed since the last stop.  There are other IDEs that do this for java.

I realize I could add a watch expression.

Summary: Seems like we're using wrong wording for the "incompatible" agents in the Agent Pool tables
Description:
Incompatible in our terminology is "lacking certain parameters". 
When the user selects a custom run policy for an agent, the message should say something like: "Customized (or restricted) run policy" to clarify the difference.
Illustrated it with two screens (attached).

Summary: AppCode:Run Configurations: provide description for architectures as names like Native, Optimized are not descriptive
Don't show the "Enabled" status in the agent pools tables
Description:
It conceals the more important "wrong status" information, like "Disconnected" or "Disabled".
If "Enabled" is not shown, the "wrong" statuses become much more visible (attached).

Summary: Do GC doesn't work properly
Description: Do GC always returns same memory size as before.

Summary: Wrap with trans tag: process string formatting operators other then %s
Description:
Currently navigation is not available for strings with %d and other formatting operators. And new string would be created again on wrapping the text even if already exists but with %s operator.

PY-110.159

For example:
django.po file contains following msgid:
{code}msgid "found %(value)d fatal error"
msgid_plural "found %(value)d fatal errors"
msgstr[0] "s'ha trobat %(value)d error fatal"
msgstr[1] "s'han trobat %(value)d errors fatals"{code}

In django code:{code}
{% blocktrans %}found {{value}} fatal error{% endblocktrans %}{code}
Navigation won't work.

On trying to wrap {code}found {{value}} fatal error{code} new django.po entry would be created: 
{code}msgid "found %(value)s fatal error"
msgstr ""{code}

Summary: Smart enter in 'ascx' file creates too many line feeds
Description:
Action inserts a lot of line feeds instead of one.

Repro solution is DNN C#, \DesktopModules\Admin\FileManager\filemanager.ascx

Summary: Inspection 'Duplicate condition on '&&' or '||'' creates false positives.
Description:
Inspection 'Duplicate condition on '&&' or '||'' creates false positives when the branches differ by only a constant.

For example:

        return dateTime.getDayOfWeek() != DateTimeConstants.SATURDAY
                && dateTime.getDayOfWeek() != DateTimeConstants.SUNDAY;

Summary: Resharper fails to filter out test via Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting.TestCategory attribute
Description: We have a large test base, some using Accessors. I'm not sure what makes this happen, but it is preventing us from using resharper 6.

Summary: Rename / move package / move classes to another package functions break project consistency
Description:
It is hard to describe, but when I used that refactoring functions I got into big trouble - a whole lot of strange things happened like:
1. disappearing imports (suddenly some of my classes can't be found)
2. wrong package names - some of the package declarations remained old
3. lost sync with Mercurial - now Mercurial thinks some of my files have been lost, some have been moved (ok), some are unknown and I really can't figure out what is the algorithm here - it just looks as if it used scala.util.Random.

So, to summarize: please look at the renaming / moving package thing and do more serious testing of it, especially on some larger project, because it is really dangerous now to use. Maybe disable it at all until it is stable.

Summary: External apklib dependencies (Maven + Android support)
Description:
I'm having a Maven Android project with an '''external''' apklib dependency. This dependency is not detected as a project dependency / external library within IDEA (build 110.137). Maybe similar to issue IDEA-70840?

This is the pom.xml

{code lang=xml}
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<project xmlns="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0"
         xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
         xsi:schemaLocation="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0 http://maven.apache.org/xsd/maven-4.0.0.xsd">
    <modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>

    <groupId>ActionBarTest</groupId>
    <artifactId>ActionBarTest</artifactId>
    <version>1.0-SNAPSHOT</version>
    <packaging>apk</packaging>

    <dependencies>
        <!-- see https://github.com/mosabua/maven-android-sdk-deployer how to install Android dependencies -->
        <dependency>
            <groupId>android</groupId>
            <artifactId>android</artifactId>
            <version>3.2_r1</version>
            <scope>provided</scope>
        </dependency>

        <dependency>
            <groupId>com.actionbarsherlock</groupId>
            <artifactId>library</artifactId>
            <version>3.3.1</version>
            <type>apklib</type>
        </dependency>
    </dependencies>

    <build>
        <finalName>${project.artifactId}</finalName>
        <pluginManagement>
            <plugins>
                <plugin>
                    <groupId>com.jayway.maven.plugins.android.generation2</groupId>
                    <artifactId>android-maven-plugin</artifactId>
                    <version>3.0.0-alpha-12</version>
                    <extensions>true</extensions>
                </plugin>
            </plugins>
        </pluginManagement>
        <plugins>
            <plugin>
                <groupId>com.jayway.maven.plugins.android.generation2</groupId>
                <artifactId>android-maven-plugin</artifactId>
                <configuration>
                    <run>
                        <debug>true</debug>
                    </run>
                    <sdk>
                        <path>${env.ANDROID_HOME}</path>
                        <platform>13</platform>
                    </sdk>
                    <undeployBeforeDeploy>true</undeployBeforeDeploy>
                </configuration>
            </plugin>
        </plugins>
    </build>

    <repositories>
        <repository>
            <id>actionbar</id>
            <url>http://r.jakewharton.com/maven/release/</url>
        </repository>
    </repositories>

</project>

Summary: Navigate from a class to its test class
Description:
It would be very nice if it'd be possible to navigate from a class to its test class (and back).

For example if the cursor is inside the class Foo, when I press some magic shortcut, then R# looks for classes with Foo as prefix and Test as suffix. e.g. FooTest, FooSpecialTest. If there are multiple targets they show the same dialog as when using for example "navigate to derived symbols".

I assume that it would even be possible to look for test classes based on the unit test runner (they know all test classes anyway).

Summary: Unit Tests can't use concepts declared in same language.
Description:
Steps:
* Create new language
* Create simple concept extending Expression
* Very important - do not build your model until you created test case. If you did - delete all *_gen folders on disk.
* Create Test aspect
* Create test BTestCase, using your custom concept
* Now - build. You should have errors in testcase generation basically indicated that your custom concept does not exist.
* Cut testcases, build, paste testcases back, build again - now it works.

This should be fixed. Test cases should have access to concepts in the same language.

As an example of the issue see git://github.com/ushkinaz/language-sugar.git , tag 0.1

Summary: DataFlow issue in "assert throws" clause
SVN: update is performed in AWT thread and takes >20 minutes
Description:
Support feedback:

IntelliJ is extremely slow (about half an hour) on updating on our 64bit-WinXP Machines.
We tried running both IntelliJ Versions (32/64 bit)  - same effect.

Reference System is a Win-XP SP3 x32 machine.
SVN Update takes some minutes on this machine only.

We investigated all possible issues listed on http://devnet.jetbrains.net/docs/DOC-192 but no result.
So here comes a CPU snapshot and our system configuration:

CPU-snapshot on FTP:

idea.exe.vmoptions:

Summary: Errors in blocktrans tag
Gradle: Try to ensure that libraries of the imported project have distinct names
Description: There is a possible case that Gradle Tooling API returns dependencies with the same names (e.g. try to import 'gradle' project itself. It contains many dependencies that point to module-specific directories called'' 'resources' ''). We want to try to generate distinct meaningful names then.

Summary: Gradle: implement 'import from gradle' processing
Description:
Input: user-defined gradle project
Output: ready to use IJ project

Summary: Gradle: support library dependencies that don't point to *.jar files
Description: There is a possible case that dependency returned by Gradle Tooling API points not to the *.jar file but to the particular directory instead (e.g. during parsing 'gradle' project itself). We want to setup such a dependency then.

Summary: Gradle: Allow to adjust project settings prior to importing
Gradle: Allow to import gradle project from 'Open project' dialog
Description:
It's possible to import gradle project only from 'New project' dialog at the moment.

The task is to allow to start importing procedure by choosing target'' 'build.gradle' ''file from'' 'Open project' ''dialog

Summary: Multiple Agents from same machine
Description:
Hi,
    I am using TeamCity for automate the build for my project & its working great. we had configure service agent to build the project. now as per the requirement i want to execute some command which can't handle by Service agent. By research i got solution that i need to start agent from the console which didn't work like a Service agent and command which i want to execute is working with Console Agent.
Now the problem is to maintain this both agents. some issues are :-
(1) How could i maintain the console agent which is stop working when it is idle and it will stop if i will log out from machine. (We have different Machine for Build so machine never shut down only we can log out from machine.)
