Description: Add corresponding support to IJ gradle plugin when gradle side is ready ([GRADLE-1846|http://issues.gradle.org/browse/GRADLE-1846] and [GRADLE-1847|http://issues.gradle.org/browse/GRADLE-1847] are implemented)

Summary: Gradle: build run configurations on 'import from gradle'
Editor: make 'select whole line on triple click' default behavior
Unexpected behavior for cmd-w (OS X)
Description: In OS X, cmd-w normally closes something (for example a window or a tab). In PhpStorm lines of code are selected. This is somewhat (read: very) annoying. It's like if cmd-v would quit the app instead of pasting content.

Summary: Window and tab switching problem
Description:
WinXP, Win7.
При переключении окон (alt+tab), например из редактора на браузер и обратно в меню IDE подсвечивается пункт File. Такое ощущение, что был нажат alt, но выпадающего списка нет - http://i29.tinypic.com/2mc61wn.jpg. Приходится жать esc, чтобы вернуть фокус в поле редактирования, т.к. вместо перемещения стрелками курсора по строкам будет происходить скролл кода.

Баг проявляется при обычной скорости переключения окон. Если делать медленно: зажать альт, аккуратно нажать таб, отпустить таб, медленно отпустить альт (посмотрели страничку в браузере), зажать альт, аккуратно нажать таб, отпустить таб, медленно отпустить альт (вернулись в IDE) - то всё ок.

Summary: Ldap integration won't work in hierarchical User Directory
Description:
We tried to activate the LDAP integration, but it works only for a subtree. There is a limit, which makes it only partly usable. Our users are not in one folder(dn), they are represented in an directory hierarchy, because there are really a lot of them. This means our users habe not the same dn pattern.
To get the pattern you have to search the user first, und then retrieve the pattern from the user.

Our query is: uid=$login$

a User Account can be (transform): 
cn=$login$,ou=f5,ou=f4,ou=f3,ou=f2,ou=f1,ou=f0,o=de
cn=$login$,ou=f4,ou=f3,ou=f2,ou=f1,ou=f0,o=de
cn=$login$,ou=f3,ou=f2,ou=f1,ou=f0,o=de

it depends upon where the user is located in the directory.
So the transform Value cannot be static and depends on the user result.

If we set the transform value to the base of all users und leaver the query at uid=$login$
Then the comes the message that authorization failed. It only works if I enter the full dn from the user into the transform field (which we only know if the user was found in our directory).

Summary: 'Mutable variable is accessible from closure' warning message is shown for the fake closure of jQuery.each statement
inspection of javascript:  window.location=window.location is not silly at all :)
Description:
hello, just using that phantastic inspection tool to pimp up my javascript.
within assignment issues there is:

 window.location=window.location;

flagged with "Variable is assignet to itself", SillyAssignmentJS

but... that does sound silly, but reliably reloads the current window in Firefox / Chrome / IE / Safari. So I recommend to not flag it as warning.

(yes, I can suppress the message for every statment, but that should be in the base system)

Harald

Summary: RedirectToAction in base MVC controller class

Description:

Missing message: configure.incompatibleComplianceForTarget in: org.aspectj.ajdt.ajc.messages

when I try to compile..
Idea 9.0.4 could do it

I start idea by 
bash 
cd to maven project root directory
open -a /Applications/IntelliJ\ IDEA\ 10.app pom.xml

I removed ~/Library/Preferences/IntelliJIdea10
And installed the Idea once again
Then I did a few changes in an other project .. waited for now..
Suddenly it works !!!!! (don't know what did it)
So I am back on Idea 10 :-)
By the way Idea 10 seems better than 9.0.4 (better graphics, faster, less questions dialogue boxes on top of each other in start up)


Update: problem still exists for a multi-module Maven projects where some modules have maven-compiler-plugin and other modules have aspectj-maven-plugin and former have lower source/target levels than latter.

Workaround: set same source/target levels in both maven-compiler-plugin and aspectj-maven-plugin.

Summary: Flex UI Designer uses incorrect default style sheet for Spark components
Description:
''Build 108.831''

From Adobe help: "The defaults.css style sheet in the frameworks.swc file applies default styles to all components. ...
The defaults.css style sheet in the spark.swc file applies default styles to the Spark components. ...
The framework style sheet is applied first, followed by the Spark style sheet. The result is that the +Spark style sheet takes precedence where overlapping style definitions occur+ because the styles are applied after the framework styles."

Consider the following mxml:

{code}
<?xml version="1.0"?>
<s:Application xmlns:fx="http://ns.adobe.com/mxml/2009"
			   xmlns:s="library://ns.adobe.com/flex/spark">
	<s:Panel/>
</s:Application>
{code}
Open it in Design View.
Select the panel.
See ''dropShadowVisible'' style. The style value is ''false'', while it is actually ''true'' for Spark Panel. Click to the style. ''default.css'' from ''frameworks.swc'' is opened instead of ''default.css'' from ''spark.swc''.

Summary: Separate Flex IDE like PHPStorm
Description:
I don't know if this is the right place to propose this idea, but perhaps it might be a nice idea to make a separate application for Flex/ActionScript/AIR development just as you guys have done for PHP with PHPStorm. I'm loving IntelliJ IDEA but I prefer PHPStorm since it has a focused task and is far less cluttered than IDEA.

Just a thought...

Summary: IDEA cannot resolve Maven executing goals
Description:
I have declared this plugin in a POM file and IDEA renders the goals in red complaining that it cannot resolve them:

{code:lang=xml}
            <plugin>
                <groupId>org.codehaus.mojo</groupId>
                <artifactId>gwt-maven-plugin</artifactId>
                <version>2.3.0-1</version>
                <executions>
                    <execution>
                        <goals>
                            <goal>compile</goal>
                            <goal>generateAsync</goal>
                            <goal>test</goal>
                        </goals>
                    </execution>
                </executions>
            </plugin>
{code}

Looks like this issue was fixed in an earlier version but it has reappeared in IDEA 10.5.2.

Summary: Default file template header is pointing to non-existing menu option on Mac OS X
Description:
Default file template header is pointing to non-existing menu option on Mac OS X:

Header:

/**
 * Created by IntelliJ IDEA.
 * User: superuser
 * Date: 10/18/11
 * Time: 5:20 PM
 * To change this template use File | Settings | File Templates.
 */

It should point to IntelliJ IDEA | Preferences | File Templates.

The template points to the proper location for the Windows version of the application.

Summary: $SelectionStartColumn$ and $SelectionEndColumn$ external tools macros count tabs as expanded spaces
Description:
When I run external tools and use the $SelectionStartColumn$ or $SelectionEndColumn$ as parameters, PhpStorm sets their values such that tab characters in the code (assuming the setting to use actual tabs is enabled) are counted as their equivalent in space characters. So for example, if tabs are set to be the equivalent of four spaces, and a single tab character precedes a line, and the cursor is right before the second non-whitespace character of the line, then $SelectionStartColumn$ will be set to the value of six instead of two.

The primary side-effect of this is that the external tool must adjust the offsets for each tab character that appears in the content. This is bad enough, but it's made worse by the fact that doing this requires knowing just how many spaces each tab counts as, a value which depends on user IDE settings - making it impossible for multiple users to share external tool scripts without modification, or even for one user to use the same script across multiple projects with different settings or across change to the setting.

What I'd expect is that $SelectionStartColumn$ and $SelectionEndColumn$ be set to values that represent actual character offsets, regardless of what the characters are. Thus, each tab (ASCII 9) character would always count as one character.

Summary: Can not generate generator with PatternList
Description: Try to use pattern list and then try to use it in CopySrc

Summary: Cursor moves after running an external tool that modifies the file
Description:
Reproduce:
1) Define an external tool that makes a modification to the current file, as indicated by $FilePath$, and ensure the option to synchronize external changes is enabled.
2) Open a file, position the cursor somewhere in the middle, and run the external tool.
3) Assuming PhpStorm picks up the change (see WI-7994), the file will update.

Observation: Unless the cursor is already at the very last line, it is moved to the line following the one where it is located. It keeps the same column, however (even if that column happens to be in the middle of a tab). This happens even when the change is such that it should have no effect on the selection range (such as when the change is adding something at the end of the file).

Expectation: When possible, the cursor should maintain its position.

Summary: Improve usability of Breakpoints by adding a "Breakpoint Panel" above the edit area
Description:
The Breakpoints dialog is tedious and the optional values are hidden during normal debugging.  I'd like to propose that you add a feature that adds a ''"Breakpoint Panel"'' whenever the cursor is on a line with a breakpoint. This breakpoint panel could be similar to how the find and replace panels work ''(which are a brilliantly usable part of PhpStorm.)''

!replace-panel.png!

In that panel I'd propose putting everything that is in the lower part of the Breakpoints dialog and also a button to load the Breakpoints dialog if the user wants to view all breakpoints.

!Breakpoints.png!

I think such a feature would really help advanced users to use conditionals, depends on and suspend breakpoints more frequently and it could also teach beginning users that these features are available.

*Bonus Points!* :-) 

If you really want to make this great please allow users to set in preferences which of these items will be displayed in the Breakpoints panel so that we can have a one-line panel instead of a two line panel (if we want), and include a link on the panel to the preferences section where these options would be available to be configured.

Also, if you be great is the breakpoints panel would have up and down arrows like the find and replace panels that would allow you to jump around between breakpoints within the same file.

Summary: Add inspection to report duplicated css-selectors and their definitions
External Tools > "Synchronize files after execution" option is unreliable
Description:
I've set up an external tool that modifies the current file. PhpStorm passes the file path and cursor position information into the file, the script reads the file, inserts some text at the selection, and then saves it back out. With the Sync option enabled, PhpStorm doesn't always recognize these changes and properly reload the file, which leaves you viewing the file with the now-outdated contents. (I can even open the file in another editor and see the new content. In fact, if I leave the file open in another editor in the background, I can see the file update immediately when the script runs in PhpStorm.) Sometimes it works, sometimes it doesn't.

My change happens very quickly, so I thought that maybe it had to do with the mod time of the file. I don't know how PhpStorm catches external modifications. So, I tried 'touch'ing the file, setting the mtime and atime to a couple of seconds in the future, but that had no effect. If I make my script sleep before returning, that seems to do the trick (albeit with much annoyance having to wait), but the time that's required varies... on some of our workstations and with some executions, one second is enough, while others require two or more seconds. 

I'm running PhpStorm under Mac OS X Server 10.7.2 on a Mac Pro 5,1.

Summary: XSLT debug: when execution point goes off the view the editor does not scroll
Description:
Provide .xsl like:
{code}
<xsl:stylesheet version="1.0" xmlns:xsl="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Transform">
	<xsl:output method="xml" indent="yes"/>

	<xsl:template match="/">
		<result>
			<test/> <!-- breakpoint -->
			<test/>
			<!-- and many more similar lines just to fill space -->
			<test/>
			<test/>
		</result>
	</xsl:template>
</xsl:stylesheet>
{code}
Set the breakpoint as marked above.
Debug (tested Saxon and Saxon 9), stop on the breakpoint.
Debug tool window opens and hides a part of XSL code.
Perform Step Over (F8) many times to move execution from line to line.

The problem is that when execution point mark (blue line) goes off the view, the editor does not scroll.
Java debugger scrolls the editor in such case.
108.743.

Immediate/interactive code execution in context during debug session
Description:
One highly desirable feature which keeps me actively using nuSphere's PhpED IDE is its 'immediate panel' in debug mode. The most widely-experienced similar feature folks are likely used to using is the 'active code execution' feature available in browser-based JavaScript debuggers. These interactive panels go by various names, often being referred to as a console window, etc.

Having spent over 25 years as a Smalltalk (pure OOP) designer/developer, I am very much a 'code as you go' type -- a prototyping, evolutionary style of coding -- kind of like laying a length of track just ahead of the locomotive while building a railroad. I very much benefit from writing code in a 'live' context. (BTW, PhpED even has a 'Set execution point' feature in its debugger which is way more Smalltalk-like than anything offered by _any_ PHP IDE. Nudge, nudge... if you super JetBrainiacs could do that, too, wow! :-)

I have just spent the last couple weeks exclusively in PhpStorm 2.0 and am _nearly_ able to be comfortable with it as my primary PHP/JavaScript IDE. Its unique strengths (and developer-active ongoing improvements) make it a welcome new addition to my 'must have' toolkit. But for these last couple weeks I have been doing much more client-side JavaScript development than server-side PHP. Now that I am moving back into a more server-side phase of my project, the lack of an 'immediate/contextual PHP code execution panel' is much more obvious to me.

WISH LIST ITEM: I believe PhpStorm 2.x would be EVEN BETTER than it already is if an 'immediate/contextual PHP code execution panel' was added to the debugging session feature-set. (For the specific PhpED feature I am referencing, see http://www.nusphere.com/products/php_debugger.htm?#call_php_function and this image, http://www.nusphere.com/graphics/php_debugger/debugger-immediate-large.png

RATIONALE: Such an interactive 'sandbox' can be invaluable to the efficiency of 'agile' and prototyping development styles. Together with PhpStorm's JavaScript debugging features, such an interactive code execution panel would further improve PhpStorm's competitive position among PHP IDEs.

Thank you for considering this wish-list request. I certainly will look forward to it being added to an uncoming release. :-)

''DropaBalm.com Jambo''

P.S. If I am simply clueless and this feature already exists in PhpStorm and I am too lame to find it, please by all means point me to it and close this wish-list feature request.

I have this declaration:

{code lang=vb}Dim newId = HelpProject.EscapeString(value){code}

{monospace}EscapeString{monospace} explicitly returns {monospace}String{monospace}, but when I am later trying to use {monospace}Ctrl+Space{monospace} after some newId usage, I get only default {monospace}Object{monospace} methods listed, and none of those of {monospace}String{monospace}, though if I'll type them manually, they're recognized by VS and code like {monospace}newId.Length.Equals(0){monospace} works fine.

Is there anything wrong?

SQL: code completion suggests keywords not valid in current position but allowed in further clauses
Description:
SQL, Derby. Consider valid statement:
{code} create table temp47 (c1 varchar (16) for bit data); {code}
Make sure Settings / Editor / Code Completion / Autopopup code completion = Yes.
Erase "data" token, put the caret there.
Type 'd' character. Get completion suggestions: "DATA, DEFAULT".
But only DATA is valid after BIT in this context.

Actually it is not an obvious bug: DEFAULT may follow somewhere after: "... BIT DATA DEFAULT NULL".
It is a question, should we suggest some maybe-following words or not. (Java completion does not do it, as I can see.)

Summary: Search in Coverage tree of R# TestRunner: text caret isn't displayed, and you can't type space
Description:
1. run coverage of any unit tests: you need Unit Test Runner window with non-empty 'Coverage' tab
2. put focus into Coverage tab
3. type anything - search panel is opened, value is typed in it, but no text caret is shown
4. press Space - space isn't typed in the search field
5. click in the search field - text caret appeared; now you can type space and navigate through text with right and left arrows.
Text caret should appear in the field immediately when the search panel is opened.

Summary: Results of Filter by Opened project differ in TeamCity Watched Projects  and Teamcity My Changes views.

Summary: Incorrect matching @end highlighting if @protocol directive is used
Custom build: allow to provide revisions for the VCS roots
Description:
Current approach to specify a revision in custom run build dialog is to choose a change from the list of detected ones.
Limitations here are:
- user might want to trigger a build on an old change that was not detected by TeamCity
- user might want to specify different revisions for different VCS roots, and these revisions are not necessarily can be derived form the single selected change.

Revision chooser should probably be per-VCS root and allow to choose detected change, enter exact revision, use "current revision" or mark root for ignorance.

--- old text:
Configuration:
a build configuration had one set of VCS roots, then the set changed and current roots are different.
in this setup choosing a change will include the changes that are "below" it in our modifications list, but that can actually include a more recent change then the selected one.

When a user in custom run dialog selects a change for which we cannot find a corresponding revision in any of the current roots (we will search in the changes linked to this build configuration and the current VCS roots), let's provide user with a list of current VCS roots and allow to choose revision for each of them.

Revision chooser should probably allow to enter exact revision, current revision or mark root for ignorance.

Later on we can allow to start a build based on existing build and use existing build's VCS settings in the dialog.

Description: Inspection "Reference before assignment" wrongly marks the usage of __debug__ as as problem. __debug__ is always defined an its value depends on the Python 'optimize' flag, see [http://docs.python.org/reference/simple_stmts.html#assert].

Summary: IMPOSSIBLE to use ReSharper on big VB.NET files
Description: We have some VB.NET files that have about 10-20K lines of code. It is impossible to edit those files with ReSharper installed because every time I type a word or a few characters in the file it takes VS about 20 seconds to do something (I assume it is trying to recompile). Without ReSharper installed this problem doesn't happen.

Summary: Support Subversion 1.7?
Description:
Please support Subversion 1.7, at least for the working copy enhancements:
http://subversion.apache.org/docs/release-notes/1.7.html
